  window.TTS_AUDIO['A habitat is where things live. A camel lives in the dry desert. A whale lives in the big ocean. Some trees stay green all year. Now show what you know!'] = base + 'grade-1-a-habitat-is-where-things-live-a-ded08a-ded08a09.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Earth rotates to make day and night. Stars make their own light. The sun gives us light and heat. The moon is rock with craters. Now show what you know!'] = base + 'grade-1-earth-rotates-to-make-day-and-night-d0313a-d0313ad9.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['All living things need water. Fish live in the water. A lake has fresh water. The ocean has salt water. Fish breathe with gills. Water goes in through the mouth. Gills take what fish need. So yes, a fish drinks water!'] = base + 'grade-1-all-living-things-need-water-fish-live-da063f-da063fa4.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Living things eat food. Food gives us energy. Energy helps us run and play. Animals eat different foods. A monkey eats bananas. A cow eats grass. A bird eats worms. A penguin eats fish. Animals eat what grows near them. So yes, monkeys eat bananas!'] = base + 'grade-1-living-things-eat-food-food-gives-us-6bd3c9-6bd3c976.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Balloons have air in them. Air is a gas. A gas is a kind of matter. You cannot see a gas. A gas takes the shape of its space. A gas has less mass than water. Helium is a gas lighter than air. A helium balloon floats up high. That is why balloons float away!'] = base + 'grade-1-balloons-have-air-in-them-air-is-3da4ed-3da4ed71.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO["The sun gives us energy. We see the energy as light. We feel the energy as heat. The sun's light helps us see. The sun's heat keeps us warm. Plants use the sun to make food. We eat plants and animals. Without the sun, nothing could grow. We need the sun to live!"] = base + 'grade-1-the-sun-gives-us-energy-we-see-45c500-45c5004b.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['When a thing moves, it follows a path. You can push a car forward. You can pull a car backward. Some paths are straight. Some paths are curved. Some paths go in a circle. Force can change a path. A steering wheel turns the wheels. So a steering wheel changes the path!'] = base + 'grade-1-when-a-thing-moves-it-follows-a-5dc067-5dc06706.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['When water freezes, it turns to ice. Ice is a solid. It keeps its shape. Heat makes ice warm up. When ice warms up, it melts. Melted ice turns into water. Heat can make water very hot. Hot water turns into steam. Steam is the gas form of water. So heat makes ice melt!'] = base + 'grade-1-when-water-freezes-it-turns-to-ice-7af216-7af216ca.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Animals eat food to live. But plants do not eat. Plants make their own food! Leaves catch the sunlight. Roots drink water from the ground. The stem holds the plant up tall. The stem carries water up high. Plants need air, water, and light. So a plant has no mouth at all!'] = base + 'grade-1-animals-eat-food-to-live-but-plants-b8f94a-b8f94a6d.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Spring comes after winter. The weather gets warmer. The days get longer. Warm air and cool air make rain. Some places get a lot of rain. Plants need warmth, light, and water. The rain helps the plants grow. Flowers begin to bloom. That is why there are flowers in spring!'] = base + 'grade-1-spring-comes-after-winter-the-weather-gets-8b60ec-8b60ec05.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['A camel lives in the desert. The desert is hot and dry. There is not much food or water. A camel stores fat in its hump. The fat helps it go a long time. Big feet help it walk on the sand. Long eyelashes keep sand out of its eyes. These body parts help the camel live here.'] = base + 'grade-1-a-camel-lives-in-the-desert-the-9b875c-9b875c50.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['When a thing moves, it is in motion. It takes force to move a thing. A force is a push or a pull. A push moves a thing away. A pull brings a thing closer. Big, heavy things need more force. A wheel is round. It rolls. Wheels make pushing easy. So a cart has wheels to roll!'] = base + 'grade-1-when-a-thing-moves-it-is-in-1a0638-1a06388a.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Some things grow. Some things do not. A puppy grows into a dog. A seed grows into a plant. Only living things grow and change. Living things need food, water, and air. These help living things survive. A rock is nonliving. It does not eat, drink, or grow. So a rock can NOT grow!'] = base + 'grade-1-some-things-grow-some-things-do-not-467087-467087ac.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Earth is the planet we live on. Earth spins all the way around. It rotates once every day. The sun and moon do not move. Our side turns to the sun. It is day. Our side turns away. It is night. At night we see the stars. Earth never stops rotating. So we always have day and night!'] = base + 'grade-1-earth-is-the-planet-we-live-on-014bea-014beab5.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Water is a liquid. A liquid is a kind of matter. When you pour a liquid, it flows. A liquid does not keep its shape. It takes the shape of its cup. When it spills, it spreads out. When you drop a liquid, it splashes! A ball bounces, but water splashes. That is why water splashes!'] = base + 'grade-1-water-is-a-liquid-a-liquid-is-f439d3-f439d389.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['The moon is close to Earth. The moon is made of rock. It has tall mountains. It has craters like big bowls. Rocks crashed in and made the craters. The moon has no air or water. So nothing can live on the moon. We must take our own air and water. The moon seems to change shape, too.'] = base + 'grade-1-the-moon-is-close-to-earth-the-c05558-c05558cc.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Winter is the coldest season. The days are shorter. Earth tilts away from the sun. We get less sunlight. A thermometer tells the temperature. Water freezes at 32 degrees. Snow is tiny frozen drops of water. Snowflakes and icicles are frozen, too. That is why it snows in the winter!'] = base + 'grade-1-winter-is-the-coldest-season-the-days-888d00-888d00f3.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['The ocean is very big. It is full of salty water. A whale lives in the ocean. A whale is the biggest ocean animal. Many whales eat tiny krill. A lake is much smaller than an ocean. Lake water is fresh, not salty. A lake is too small for a big whale. So a whale cannot live in a lake!'] = base + 'grade-1-the-ocean-is-very-big-it-is-fc9429-fc9429bf.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Force makes a ball move. Distance is how far it goes. A big kick is a big force. A big force sends the ball far. A little tap is a little force. A little force goes a short way. Speed is how fast a thing moves. An airplane is fast. A snail is slow. So a hard kick makes a ball go far!'] = base + 'grade-1-force-makes-a-ball-move-distance-is-3cc621-3cc6219c.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['At night we see stars shining. Stars give off their own light. The sun is a star, too. The sun is the closest star to us. We see the moon at night. The moon is made of rock. The moon does not make its own light. Light from the sun makes it bright. Planets like Mars reflect the sun, too.'] = base + 'grade-1-at-night-we-see-stars-shining-stars-e8271f-e8271f9b.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Each year has four seasons. Summer is the warmest season. Earth tilts on its axis. Earth orbits, or goes around, the sun. In summer, Earth tilts toward the sun. We get a lot of sunshine. The sunshine makes the days hot. It makes the days longer, too. That is why it is hot in the summer!'] = base + 'grade-1-each-year-has-four-seasons-summer-is-298fd1-298fd16a.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Fall comes after summer. Another name for fall is autumn. The weather gets colder. The days get shorter. There is less sunlight for leaves. Leaves turn red, yellow, and brown. Cool, dry air makes wind. The wind blows the leaves off the trees. That is why trees lose their leaves in fall!'] = base + 'grade-1-fall-comes-after-summer-another-name-for-3b8590-3b85901d.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Throw a ball up. It comes down. A force pulls it to the ground. That force is called gravity. Gravity pulls everything down. It pulls all things the same way. A ball and a book fall the same. Your force can hold things up. A slide changes your path down. So gravity makes things fall down!'] = base + 'grade-1-throw-a-ball-up-it-comes-down-e9ffcd-e9ffcd91.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['A habitat is a place where animals live. There are many habitats on Earth. A forest is full of trees and plants. A bird sleeps in a nest. A fox sleeps in a den. A desert is very hot and dry. A snake hides under a warm rock. The ocean is full of salty water. A fish can even sleep underwater!'] = base + 'grade-1-a-habitat-is-a-place-where-animals-d36086-d3608669.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['All trees have leaves. Leaves come in many shapes. Flat leaves soak up the warm sun. In the fall, they turn red and orange. Then they dry up and fall off. An evergreen grows in cold places. It has thin leaves like needles. These leaves stay green all year. Leaves match the place where the tree lives.'] = base + 'grade-1-all-trees-have-leaves-leaves-come-in-1d188d-1d188de7.wav';
  window.TTS_AUDIO['Everything is made of matter. A solid is one kind of matter. A solid keeps its own shape. A ball stays a ball. A wall stays a wall. A wall is a solid. So are you! You can mix solids into a mixture. Each solid keeps its shape in the mix. Two solids cannot share one spot. So we cannot walk through a wall!'] = base + 'grade-1-everything-is-made-of-matter-a-solid-e535dc-e535dc46.wav';
